class
button

.but - creates a basic button
.but-elegant - adds box-shadow to the button and creates a black background
.but-drop - changes background when focused
.but-fancy - creates moving borders on the button and borders become inactive when a button is clicked

badges
.nbadge - creates a badge
.c-rotate - rotates a badge clockwise (c- clockwise)
.a-rotate - rotates a badge anti-clockwise (a- anti clockwise)
.b-a-rotate - break and rotate on innerupdate and apply .jbut on the button for number increament

//js

<label>Choose an ice cream flavor:
  <select class="ice-cream" name="ice-cream">
    <option value="">Select One â€¦</option>
    <option value="chocolate">Chocolate</option>
    <option value="sardine">Sardine</option>
    <option value="vanilla">Vanilla</option>
  </select>
</label>

<div class="result"></div>


const selectElement = document.querySelector('.ice-cream');

selectElement.addEventListener('change', (event) => {
  const result = document.querySelector('.result');
  result.textContent = `You like ${event.target.value}`;
});

